Heat a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @pulled pork{8%ounce} and @Tex-Mex paste{1}; cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until warmed through, ~{3-4%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, wash and dry produce.

Dice @tomato{1} into ¼-inch pieces. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Quarter @lime{1}.

> Pressed for time? Skip chopping the cilantro—instead, tear it by hand and sprinkle over top before serving!

In a #small bowl{}, combine tomato, chopped cilantro, and juice from half the lime.

Divide @blue corn tortilla chips{3%ounce} between #bowls{}; top with Tex-Mex pulled pork, @Mexican cheese blend{1/2%cup}, pico de gallo, and @guacamole{4%tablespoon}. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.

   > Pulled Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.